    • Method Detail

      • setUp

        public void setUp()
        Initiates the values for SimpleProjectile class. It has following instances:
        • projectile1: When particle is at initial position x=0.00, y=0.0, x-velocity component = 0.00 and y-velocity component = 10.00
        • projectile1: When particle is at initial position x=1.32224, y=4.2332, x-velocity component = 2.120 and y-velocity component = 20.00
        • projectile1: When particle is at initial position x=-1.32224, y=-4.2332, x-velocity component = 2.120 and y-velocity component = 30.23745544

      • testState1

        public void testState1()
        This test case will pass if the output state has the same value as the desired state. It checks for the condition where provided time = restTime (restTime is the time at which particle will be at "rest" for the first time).

      • testState2

        public void testState2()
        This test case will fail if the output state has the same value as the desired state. It checks for the condition where time is greater than restTime (restTime is the time at which particle will be at "rest" for the first time).

      • testState3

        public void testState3()
        This test case will fail if the output state has the same value as the desired state. It checks for the condition where time is less than restTime (restTime is the time at which particle will be at "rest" for the first time)

      • testState4

        public void testState4()
        This test case will fail if the output state has the same value as the non-desired state. It checks for the condition where initial x, y positions and x, y velocity component has some positive values. Also, time is greater than restTime.

      • testState5

        public void testState5()
        This test case will fail if the output state has the same value as the non-desired state. It checks for the condition where initial x, y positions and x, y velocity component has some negative values. Also, time is less than restTime.

      • testState6

        public void testState6()
        This test case will fail if the output state has the same value as the non-desired state. It checks for the condition where initial x, y positions and x, y velocity component has some negative values. Also, time is greater than restTime
